Werner,

The documentation for the Fortran interface has not been updated in  
quite a while.

But if you want to do zero-D reactor simulations, I would recommend  
doing them  in Python.  The Python interface is documented.  If you  
are using Windows, on the Start menu under &quot;Python&quot; there is an  
option to view module documentation; select this and navigate to  
Cantera, then look at class Reactor. On unix or mac, type &quot;pydoc -g&quot;  
from the command line to access the Python documentation.  Also,  
there are several working demo scripts that show how to do zero-D  
reactor simulations. Take a look in demos/python/reactors (or if you  
have the Cantera source code, these are in Cantera/python/examples/ 
reactors).

Dave

